obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (57234)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57234&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Commission for Air`
  line `Quality Management in National Capital Region and Adjoining Areas Act, 2021.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall apply to the National Capital Region and also to adjoining areas in so far as it relates to`
  line `matters concerning air pollution in the National Capital Region.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 13th April, 2021.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (57235)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57235&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "adjoining areas" means the areas in the States of Haryana, Punjab, Rajasthan and Uttar Pradesh,`
  line `adjoining the National Capital Territory of Delhi and the National Capital Region, where any source of`
  line `pollution is located, causing adverse impact on air quality in the National Capital Region;`
  line
  line `(b) "Associate Member" means a member who is co-opted under sub-section (3) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Commission for Air Quality Management in`
  line `National Capital Region and Adjoining Areas referred to in section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "Commission"means the Commission for Air Quality Management in National Capital Region`
  line `and Adjoining Areas constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(e) "Member" means a Member of the Commission and includes the Chairperson thereof;`
  line
  line `(f) "National Capital Region"shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (f) of section`
  line `2 of the National Capital Region Planning Board Act, 1985 (2 of 1985);`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The words used herein and not defined, but defined in the Environment (Protection) Act, 1986 (26`
  line `of 1986), shall have the meaning as assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (57236)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57236&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, constitute a body to be known as the Commission for Air Quality Management in National Capital`
  line `Region and Adjoining Areas to exercise the powers conferred upon, and to perform the functions assigned`
  line `to, that Commission under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall consist of the following Members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) a full-time Chairperson having experience of not less than fifteen years in the field of`
  line `environment protection and pollution control or having administrative experience of not less than`
  line `twenty-five years;`
  line
  line `(b) a representative of the Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry of Environment,`
  line `Forest and Climate Change, who shall be an officer not below the rank of Joint Secretary, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) five ex officio Members who are either Chief Secretaries, or Secretaries in-charge of the`
  line `department dealing with environment protection in the National Capital Territory of Delhi and the`
  line `States of Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan and Uttar Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(d) one full-time Member who is or has been a Joint Secretary to the Government of India;`
  line
  line `(e) three full-time independent technical Members to be appointed from amongst persons having`
  line `specific knowledge and experience in matters relating to air pollution;`
  line
  line `(f) one technical Member from the Central Pollution Control Board, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) one technical Member to be nominated by the Indian Space Research Organisation, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) three Members from non-Governmental organisations having experience in matters concerning`
  line `combating of air pollution;`
  line
  line `(i) one representative of the National Institution for Transforming India, not below the rank of Joint`
  line `Secretary or Adviser, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(j) one officer in the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India to be appointed by the`
  line `Central Government as a full-time Member-Secretary of the Commission;`
  line
  line `(k) three members, being stakeholders from such sectors as agriculture, industry, transport or`
  line construction.
  line
  line `(3) The Commission may co-opt the following persons as Associate Members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a representative of the Ministry of Road Transport and Highways, not below the rank of Joint`
  line `Secretary to the Government of India;`
  line
  line `(b) a representative of the Ministry of Power, not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India;`
  line
  line `(c) a representative of the Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs, not below the rank of Joint`
  line `Secretary to the Government of India;`
  line
  line `(d) a representative of the Ministry of Petroleum and Natural Gas, not below the rank of Joint`
  line `Secretary to the Government of India;`
  line
  line `(e) a representative of the Ministry of Agriculture and Farmers Welfare, not below the rank of`
  line `Joint Secretary to the Government of India;`
  line
  line `(f) a representative of the Ministry of Commerce and Industry, not below the rank of Joint Secretary`
  line `to the Government of India;`
  line
  line `(g) a representative of any association of commerce or industry;`
  line
  line `(h) such other Associate Members, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Member-Secretary shall be the Chief Co-ordinating Officer of the Commission and shall assist`
  line `the Commission in the discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The headquarters of the Commission shall be at Delhi and the Commission may, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government, establish offices at other places in the National Capital Region or`
  line `adjoining areas.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, and`
  line `notwithstanding any judgment or order of any court, the Commission shall have exclusive jurisdiction in`
  line `the National Capital Region and adjoining areas in respect of matters covered by this Act and no other body,`
  line `authority, individual or committee shall have any power or jurisdiction in such matters:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of any conflict in the orders or directions of the Commission and the Governments`
  line `of the National Capital Territory of Delhi and of the States of Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan and Uttar Pradesh`
  line `or the Central Pollution Control Board or the State Pollution Control Boards of the States of Punjab,`
  line `Haryana, Rajasthan and Uttar Pradesh or the Pollution Control Committee of the National Capital Territory of Delhi or any other statutory authority set up or established under a State Act, the order as well as the`
  line `direction of the Commission shall prevail.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (57237)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of Chairperson, Members and Member-Secretary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57237&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The full-time Chairperson`
  line `and full-time Members, other than ex officio Members, of the Commission shall be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that every appointment under this sub-section shall, subject to the provisions of second`
  line `proviso, be made on the recommendations of a Selection Committee consisting of---`
  line
  line `(a) Minister in-charge of the Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change in the`
  line `Government of India--Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) Minister in-charge of the Ministry of Commerce and Industry in the Government of India--`
  line member;
  line
  line `(c) Minister in-charge of the Ministry of Road Transport and Highways in the Government of India--member;`
  line
  line `(d) Minister in-charge of the Ministry of Science and Technology in the Government of India--`
  line member;
  line
  line `(e) Cabinet Secretary--member:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case where the Central Government appoints a serving officer as the`
  line `Chairperson under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 3, or the full-time Member under clause (d)`
  line `thereof, then, no recommendation of the Selection Committee shall be required.`
  line
  line `(2) No appointment of the Chairperson or a Member shall be invalid merely by reason of any vacancy`
  line `of any member in the Selection Committee referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The appointment of the Member-Secretary of the Commission shall be made by the Central`
  line `Government in such manner, subject to such terms and conditions, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (57238)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Resignation and removal of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57238&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson or a Member,`
  line `other than an ex officio Member, may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the Central`
  line `Government, resign his office.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may remove the Chairperson or any Member, other than an ex officio`
  line `Member, from his office, in such manner as may be prescribed, if such person---`
  line
  line `(a) is adjudged an insolvent;`
  line
  line `(b) engages during his term of office in any paid employment outside the duties of his office;`
  line
  line `(c) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(d) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public interest;`
  line
  line `(e) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions; or`
  line
  line `(f) is convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government involves moral turpitude:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such Member shall be so removed, unless he has been given an opportunity of being`
  line heard.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (57239)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57239&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson or a Member, other than an`
  line `ex officio Member, shall hold office for a term of three years from the date on which he enters upon his`
  line `office or until he attains the age of seventy years, whichever is earlier, and shall be eligible for`
  line re-appointment.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (57240)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Member to act as Chairperson or to discharge his functions in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57240&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `1) In`
  line `the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairperson by reason of death, resignation`
  line `or otherwise, the Central Government may, by notification, authorise one of the Members to act as the`
  line `Chairperson until the appointment of a new Chairperson to fill such vacancy.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Chairperson is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence on leave or otherwise,`
  line `such one of the Members as the Central Government may, by notification, authorise in this behalf, shall`
  line `discharge the functions of the Chairperson until the date on which the Chairperson resumes his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (57241)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57241&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The salaries and allowances`
  line `payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the Chairperson and Members, other than`
  line `ex officio Members, shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson or a Member shall be varied to his disadvantage after his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (57242)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57242&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceedings of the`
  line `Commission shall be invalidated merely on the ground of existence of any vacancy or defect in the`
  line `constitution of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (57243)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Procedure to be regulated by Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57243&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall meet at such time and`
  line `place as the Chairperson may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, the Commission shall have the`
  line `power to lay down by regulations its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(3) All orders and decisions of the Commission shall be authenticated by the Member-Secretary or any`
  line `other officer of the Commission duly authorised by the Chairperson in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission may, by general or special order, subject to such conditions and limitations, if any,`
  line `as may be specified therein, delegate to the Chairperson, full-time Member, Member-Secretary or any`
  line `Sub-Committee constituted under section 11, such of its powers under this Act (except the power to make`
  line `regulations under section 25), as it may deem necessary or expedient for the purpose of protecting and`
  line `improving the quality of the air in the National Capital Region and adjoining areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (57244)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Sub-Committees and other staff of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57244&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall have at least the`
  line `following three Sub-Committees---`
  line
  line `(a) Sub-Committee on Monitoring and Identification;`
  line
  line `(b) Sub-Committee on Safeguarding and Enforcement;`
  line
  line `(c) Sub-Committee on Research and Development.`
  line
  line `(2) The Sub-Committee on Monitoring and Identification shall be headed by a Member of the`
  line `Commission chosen by it and shall have the following additional members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) one representative from the Central Pollution Control Board;`
  line
  line `(b) one representative each from the State Pollution Control Board or Committee, as the case`
  line `may be, of the National Capital Territory of Delhi and the States of Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan`
  line `and Uttar Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(c) one representative from the National Environmental Engineering Research Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) such other members as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Sub-Committee on Safeguarding and Enforcement shall be headed by the full-time Chairperson`
  line `of the Commission and shall have the following additional members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) one representative each, not below the rank of Secretary from the department tackling air`
  line `pollution from the National Capital Territory of Delhi and the States of Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan and`
  line `Uttar Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(b) one representative each from the State Pollution Control Board or Committee, as the case may`
  line `be, from the National Capital Territory of Delhi and the States of Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan and Uttar`
  line Pradesh;
  line
  line `(c) one officer not below the rank of Inspector General of Police or equivalent from the National`
  line `Capital Territory of Delhi and the States of Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan and Uttar Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(d) such other members as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) The Sub-Committee on Research and Development shall be headed by a full-time technical Member`
  line `of the Commission and shall have the following additional Members, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) two technical representatives from the National Environmental Engineering Research Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) one technical representative each from research institutions or Universities or colleges or`
  line `organisations in the National Capital Territory of Delhi and the States of Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan`
  line `and Uttar Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(c) two technical representatives from the field of medicine and research working or studying on`
  line `the impact of air pollution on living beings;`
  line
  line `(d) such other members as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commission may also constitute such other Sub-Committees as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(6) The members of the Sub-Committees, other than ex officio members, shall be paid such allowances`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government, in consultation with the Commission, shall determine the nature and the`
  line `categories of officers and other staff required to assist the Commission in the discharge of its function and`
  line `provide the Commission with such officers and employees as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(8) The officers and other staff of the Commission shall discharge their duties and functions under the`
  line `general superintendence of the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(9) The salaries, allowances and conditions of service of the officers and other staff appointed under`
  line `sub-section (7) shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (57245)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Powers and functions of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57245&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, the Commission shall have the power to take all such measures, issue directions`
  line `and entertain complaints, as it deems necessary or expedient, for the purpose of protecting and improving`
  line `the quality of the air in the National Capital Region and adjoining areas and shall also have the duty to take`
  line `all such measures as may become necessary for protecting and improving the quality of air in the National`
  line `Capital Region and adjoining areas.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of sub-section (1), the Commission shall, for`
  line `the purposes of sub-section (1), have the following powers to perform its duties, including taking measures`
  line `to abate air pollution and to regulate or prohibit activities that are likely to cause or increase air pollution`
  line `in the National Capital Region and adjoining areas, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) co-ordination of actions by the Governments of the National Capital Territory of Delhi and the`
  line `States of Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan and Uttar Pradesh, officers and other authorities under this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder or under any other law for the time being in force, which is relatable to the`
  line `objects of this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) planning and execution of a programme for the region for prevention, control and abatement of`
  line `air pollution;`
  line
  line `(iii) laying down parameters for the quality of air in its various aspects;`
  line
  line `(iv) laying down parameters for emission or discharge of environmental pollutants from various`
  line `sources whatsoever that have implications on air quality in the region:`
  line
  line `Provided that different parameters for emission or discharge may be laid down under this clause`
  line `from different sources having regard to the quality or composition of the emission or discharge of`
  line `environmental pollutants from such sources that have implications on air quality in the region;`
  line
  line `(v) restriction of areas in which any industries, operations or processes or class of industries,`
  line `operations or processes, that have implications on air quality in the region, shall not be carried out or`
  line `shall be carried out subject to certain safeguards;`
  line
  line `(vi) carrying out and requiring investigations and research relating to problems of environmental`
  line `pollution that have implications on air quality in the region;`
  line
  line `(vii) inspection of any premises, plant, equipment, machinery, manufacturing or other processes,`
  line `materials or substances and giving, by order, of such directions to such authorities, officers or persons`
  line `as it may consider necessary to take steps for the prevention, control and abatement of air pollution in`
  line `the region;`
  line
  line `(viii) collection and dissemination of information in respect of matters relating to air pollution in`
  line `the region;`
  line
  line `(ix) preparation of manuals or codes or guidelines relating to the prevention, control and abatement`
  line `of air pollution in the region;`
  line
  line `(x) appoint officers, with prior approval of the Central Government, with such designations, as it`
  line `thinks fit, for the purposes of this Act and may entrust to them such of the powers and functions under`
  line `this Act or for the purposes of achieving the objects of this Act, as it may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(xi) issue directions in writing to any person, officer or any authority and such person, officer or`
  line `authority shall be bound to comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For avoidance of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power to issue directions`
  line `under this section includes the power to direct---`
  line
  line `(a) the closure, prohibition or regulation of any industry, operation or process; or`
  line
  line `(b) stoppage or regulation of the supply of electricity or water or any other service.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) Subject to the provisions of this section, any person authorised by the Commission`
  line `in this behalf shall have a right to enter, at all reasonable times, and with such assistance as he`
  line `considers necessary, any place, for the purpose of--`
  line
  line `(i) performing any of the functions of the Commission entrusted to him;`
  line
  line `(ii) determining whether and if so, in what manner any such functions are to be performed`
  line `or whether any provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder or any notice, order,`
  line `direction or authorisation served, made, given or granted under this Act is being or has been`
  line `complied with;`
  line
  line `(iii) examining and testing any equipment, industrial plant, record, register, document or`
  line `any other material object or for conducting a search of any building in which he has reasons`
  line `to believe that an offence under this Act or the rules made thereunder has been or is being or`
  line `is about to be committed and for seizing any such equipment, industrial plant, record, register,`
  line `document or other material object if he has reasons to believe that it may furnish evidence to`
  line `the Commission of an offence punishable under this Act or the rules made thereunder or that`
  line `such seizure is necessary to prevent or mitigate environmental pollution;`
  line
  line `(b) every person carrying on any industry, operation or process or handling any hazardous`
  line `substance shall be bound to render all assistance to the person empowered by the Commission`
  line `under clause (a) for carrying out the functions under that clause and if he fails to do so without`
  line `any reasonable cause or excuse, he shall be guilty of an offence under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) if any person wilfully delays or obstructs any person authorised by the Commission under`
  line `clause (a) in the performance of his functions, he shall be guilty of an offence under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply to any`
  line `search or seizure under this section as they apply to any search or seizure made under the authority`
  line `of a warrant issued under section 94 of the said Code or, as the case may be, under the`
  line `corresponding provisions of the said law.`
  line
  line `(4) (a) The Commission or any officer authorised by it in this behalf, shall, for the purpose`
  line `of analysis, have power to take samples of air from any factory, premises or other place in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) the result of any analysis of a sample taken under clause (a) shall not be admissible`
  line `in evidence in any legal proceeding unless the provisions of clauses (c) and (d) are complied`
  line with;
  line
  line `(c) subject to the provisions of clause (d), the person taking the sample under clause (a)`
  line shall,---
  line
  line `(i) serve on the occupier or his agent or person in-charge of the place, a notice, then and`
  line `there, in such form as may be prescribed, of his intention to have it so analysed;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the presence of the occupier or his agent or person, collect a sample for analysis;`
  line
  line `(iii) cause the sample to be placed in a container or containers which shall be marked and`
  line `sealed and shall also be signed both by the person taking the sample and the occupier or his`
  line `agent or person;`
  line
  line `(iv) send without delay, the container or the containers to the laboratory established or`
  line `recognised by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) when a sample is taken for analysis under clause (a) and the person taking the sample`
  line `serves on the occupier or his agent or person, a notice under sub-clause (i) of clause (c), then, --`
  line
  line `(i) in a case where the occupier, his agent or person wilfully absents himself, the person`
  line `taking the sample shall collect the sample for analysis to be placed in a container or containers`
  line `which shall be marked and sealed and shall also be signed by the person taking the sample; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in a case where the occupier or his agent or person present at the time of taking the`
  line `sample refuses to sign the marked and sealed container or containers of the sample as required`
  line `under sub-clause (iii) of clause (c), the marked and sealed container or containers shall be`
  line `signed by the person taking the samples,-`
  line
  line `and the container or containers shall be sent without delay by the person taking the sample for analysis to`
  line `the laboratory established or recognised by the Central Government and such person shall inform the`
  line `Government Analyst appointed or recognised, about the wilful absence of the occupier or his agent or`
  line `person, or, as the case may be, his refusal to sign the container or containers.`
  line
  line `(5) In discharge of its functions and exercising of its authority, the Commission and the Sub-Committees mentioned in section 11 shall be bound by such general or specific directions of the Central`
  line `Government, as may be issued from time to time.`
  line
  line `(6) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the Commission`
  line `shall perform all or any of the following functions, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) take up matters suo motu, or on the basis of complaints made by any individual, representative`
  line `body or organisation functioning in the field of environment, against any individual, association,`
  line `company, public undertaking or local body carrying on any industry, operation or process;`
  line
  line `(b) provide the mechanism and the means to implement in the National Capital Region and`
  line `adjoining areas---`
  line
  line `(i) the National Clean Air Programme;`
  line
  line `(ii) the National Air Quality Monitoring Programme;`
  line
  line `(iii) the National Ambient Air Quality Standards;`
  line
  line `(c) provide an effective framework and platform in the National Capital Region and adjoining areas`
  line for---
  line
  line `(i) source identification of air pollutants on a periodic basis;`
  line
  line `(ii) taking on-ground steps for curbing air pollution;`
  line
  line `(iii) specific research and development in the field of air pollution;`
  line
  line `(iv) synergising the energies and efforts of all stakeholders in developing innovative ways to`
  line `monitor, enforce and research on the issues concerning air pollution;`
  line
  line `(v) building a network between technical institutions working or researching in the field of air`
  line pollution;
  line
  line `(vi) international co-operation including sharing of international best practices in the field of`
  line `air pollution;`
  line
  line `(vii) training and creating a special work-force for tackling the problem of air pollution;`
  line
  line `(d) provide an effective frame work, action plan and take appropriate steps for`
  line
  line `(i) tackling the problem of stubble burning;`
  line
  line `(ii) monitoring, assessing and inspecting air polluting agents;`
  line
  line `(iii) increasing plantation;`
  line
  line `(e) monitoring the measures taken by the States to prevent stubble burning;`
  line
  line `(f) undertake and promote research in the field of air pollution;`
  line
  line `(g) spread awareness regarding air pollution among various sections of society and promote awareness`
  line `of the collective steps that the public may take through publications, the media, seminars and other available`
  line means;
  line
  line `(h) encourage the efforts of non-governmental organisations and institutions working in the field of air`
  line pollution;
  line
  line `(i) any other functions as have been entrusted to any ad hoc committee or commission or task force or`
  line `body formed for the purpose of dealing with issues concerning air pollution, stubble burning or the`
  line `monitoring of related factors, in pursuance of any judicial order passed from time to time;`
  line
  line `(j) such other functions as it may consider necessary for the prevention of air pollution in the National`
  line `Capital Region and adjoining areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (57246)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57246&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall furnish to the Central Government an annual report`
  line `containing such details of the steps taken, proposals made, researches awaited and other measures`
  line `undertaken by it in pursuance of its functions under section 12, in such form and manner as may be specified`
  line `by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall cause the annual report furnished under sub-section (1) to be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (57247)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Penalty for contravention of provisions of Act, rules, order or direction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57247&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any noncompliance or contravention of any provisions of this Act, rules made thereunder or any order or direction`
  line `issued by the Commission, shall be an offence punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend`
  line `up to five years or with fine which may extend up to one crore rupees or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this section shall not apply to any farmer for causing air pollution by`
  line `stubble burning or mismanagement of agricultural residue.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the`
  line `offence under this Act shall be non-cognizable and triable by the Jurisdictional Judicial Magistrate of the`
  line `First Class, who shall not take cognizance of the offence except upon a complaint made by the Commission`
  line `or any officer authorised by the Commission in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any offence under this Act has been committed by a company, every person who, at the time`
  line `when the offence was committed, was directly in-charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the`
  line `conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence`
  line `and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that`
  line `he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of sub-sections (3) and (4),---`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate, and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by any Department of the Government, the`
  line `Head of the Department shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded`
  line `against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall render such Head of the Department liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all due`
  line `diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (5), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Department of Government and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any officer, other than the Head of`
  line `the Department, such officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `(7) For the purpose of this section and the procedure to be followed thereunder, the provisions of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (57248)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Environmental compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57248&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Commission may impose and collect environmental`
  line `compensation from farmers causing air pollution by stubble burning, at such rate and in such manner, as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (57249)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57249&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, after due appropriation`
  line `made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Commission by way of grants such sums of money as`
  line `the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission may spend such sums as it thinks fit for performing the functions under this Act,`
  line `and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the grants referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (57250)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57250&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Commission to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection with`
  line `the audit of the accounts of the Commission under this Act shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the`
  line `production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of`
  line `the offices of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Commission, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government by the Commission and the Central Government shall cause the audit`
  line `report to be laid, as soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (57251)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57251&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `An appeal shall lie to the National Green Tribunal constituted under the National Green`
  line `Tribunal Act, 2010 (19 of 2010) against any order, direction or action taken by or on behalf of the`
  line `Commission constituted under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (57252)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Constitution of special investigation teams.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57252&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, or any judicial order by any Court, where the Commission considers it`
  line `necessary so to do, it may constitute one or more special investigation teams, consisting of such officers or`
  line `such persons, as it thinks necessary, for the purposes of carrying out its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (57253)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power of Central Government to issue direction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57253&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, but subject to the provision of this Act, the Central Government may`
  line `issue in writing such direction, as it deems fit, to the Commission or any person, officer or authority`
  line `authorised by the Commission, and the Commission, person, or authority, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `bound to comply with such direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (57254)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power of Central Government to call for information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57254&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, from`
  line `time to time, call for such information and reports from the Commission, as it deems fit and the Commission`
  line `shall be bound to provide such information and report.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (57255)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57255&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit, proceeding or`
  line `dispute pertaining to or arising out of the actions taken or directions issued by the Commission in respect`
  line `of any matter which the Commission is empowered by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (57256)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57256&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `Central Government, the Commission, or any Member thereof, or any person acting under the direction of`
  line `either the Central Government or the Commission in respect of anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of any rules or any order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (57257)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Members and officers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57257&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Every Member of the Commission and every`
  line `officer appointed or authorised by the Commission to exercise functions under this Act shall be deemed to`
  line `be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (57258)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57258&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the other Associate Members under clause (h) of sub-section (3) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of removal of Chairperson or a Member under sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and Members under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(d) the allowance payable to the members, other than ex officio members of the Sub-Committees,`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) the appointment of officers and other staff under sub-section (7) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(f) the salaries, allowances and conditions of service of the officers and other staff under sub-section`
  line `(9) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of taking samples under clause (a) and the form of notice under sub-clause (i) of`
  line `clause (c), of sub-section (4) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(h) the rate at which, and the manner in which, the environmental compensation shall be imposed`
  line `and collected under section 15;`
  line
  line `(i) the form in which annual statement of accounts shall be prepared under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 17;
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment`
  line `shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (57259)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of Commission to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57259&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `rules made thereunder, the Commission may, with the previous approval of the Central Government, by`
  line `notification, make regulations to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed by the Commission under sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions and limitations subject to which power may be delegated by the Commission`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(c) the members of each Sub-Committee under sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(d) the form and the manner of furnishing annual report under section 13;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which has to be, or may be, specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation made by the Commission under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (57260)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57260&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions, not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years from`
  line `the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (57261)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57261&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force, any document,`
  line `judgment, order, bye-law, rule, regulation, notification having the force of law in the territory of India.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or any judgment`
  line `or any order of any Court and subject to the provisions of this Act, upon the notification of the constitution`
  line `of the Commission under section 3, no other individual or body or authority constituted either under a law`
  line `enacted by Parliament, or by a State, or appointed or nominated in terms of any judicial order, shall act`
  line `upon or have jurisdiction in relation to the matters covered by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (57317)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Repeal and savings of order constituting Environment Pollution (Prevention and Control) Authority for National Capital Region.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57317&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Order made under section 3 of the Environment`
  line `(Protection) Act, 1986 (29 of 1986) constituting the Environment Pollution (Prevention and Control)`
  line `Authority for the National Capital Region vide notification number S.O. 93(E), dated the 29th January,`
  line `1998 is hereby repealed and the Environment Pollution (Prevention and Control) Authority for the National`
  line `Capital Region is hereby dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken by the Environment Pollution`
  line `(Prevention and Control) Authority for the National Capital Region under the said Order, shall be deemed`
  line `to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (57263)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57263&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding the cessation of the Commission for Air Quality Management in`
  line `National Capital Region and Adjoining Areas Ordinance, 2020 (Ord. 13 of 2020), anything done or any`
  line `action taken under the Ordinance so ceased, shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the`
  line `corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (57264)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666&sectionId=57264&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_0_00011_202129_1629266138666
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission for Air Quality Management in National Capital`
  line `Region and Adjoining Areas Ordinance, 2021 (Ord. 4 of 2021) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the Commission for Air`
  line `Quality Management in National Capital Region and Adjoining Areas Ordinance, 2021 (Ord. 4 of 2021)`
  line `shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `राष्ट्रीय राजधानी क्षेत्र और निकटवर्ती क्षेत्रों में वायु क्वालिटी प्रबंध आयोग अधिनियम, 2021`
